Abstract

The “Guess The Number” project is a simple console-based game developed using the C programming language.
In this game, the computer generates a random number between 1 and 100, and the player has to guess the correct number
within 5 attempts. After every guess, the program gives hints whether the guessed number is too high or too low. 
The project demonstrates the use of loops, conditional statements, random number generation, and user interaction in C programming. 
This project is useful for beginners to understand basic programming concepts and game logic implementation.
